message: Extreme arrogance and ignorance, repetitive vandalism of article.

Please stop as this is completely unnecessary, at least state why you are doing this. All I am doing is changing the order of statement as it deserves to be in the opening paragraph.
You haven't even read my changes you are clearly just being biased.

I am slightly changing the order it is just a minor edit. The fact that he is one of the greatest midfielders of his generation is pretty important and should be stated in the opening paragraph of the lead like it is for many other players do your research please.
There you go, it no longer states it twice but it is important that it is mentioned in the opening.

For both Lampard and Gerrard it is mentioned more than once and in the opening paragraph and for many other footballing greats, why should't it be the same for Scholes? Furthermore, why do you keep wasting your time by deleting 'widely regarded' to 'regarded'.
